post_text:
If you are looking for a part-time job that aligns with your SLSD child's school calendar, we have an opportunity for you! SLSD Food Service is looking for part time cooks to assist with serving lunch in our kitchens. Shifts are generally about 3 hours a day and are almost exclusively on days where students are in attendance - so virtually no need for child care! You'll even get the chance to see your child and their friends at school when they come through the lunch line!

Current openings are at Harrison Elementary and Harrison Junior School, though more openings could arise either this year or when moving in to our new buildings for 2021!

More information is available at this link: https://www.southwestschools.org/departments/hr---employment-9/view-open-classified-positions-38/

post_text:
From our friends at Church on Fire:

Highlighter is coming!

"What's Highlighter", you ask?
Highlighter is a back-to-school event, hosted at Church on Fire for students that have a need for school supplies.

It's on Friday, August 7th from 6-8 p.m.

We decided to make some changes this year to make sure that everyone was still able to get supplies, and also stay as safe as possible!

So... this year we will be hosting a drive-through school supply distribution. Supplies will be for any student in ANY district grade K-12. We will hold the drive-through supply distribution at Church on Fire in Harrison, OH (10544 Harrison Ave., Harrison, OH 45030) You will enter the line through the backside of the old KMart Plaza (next to Frischs).

Even though it won't be our normal huge party, we will still have fun ways for your kids to engage with the event while waiting in line in your car. Covid isn't going to take ALL our fun!

We hope to see you then! Please, invite some friends and anyone you think might need some help!

Southwest Local School District elementary Field Days are always one of the highlights of the end of the school year. Of course, they were cancelled due to the COVID-19 (Coronavirus) school closures.

To keep this annual tradition alive, SLSD P.E. teachers coordinated "Family Field Day" activities which could be done at home. Families were asked to send in pictures and videos highlighting ways they are staying active while staying home!

Click the link below and enjoy the show. You might even pick up some ideas to try at your home this summer!

WHHHS Alumni Association
April 23 at 10:27 AM ·

The 138th annual Wm. Henry Harrison High School Alumni Association is scheduled for Saturday, May 30, 2020. Due to COVID-19, we will not be having our traditional dinner with the meeting. This year the William Henry Harrison Alumni Association will only have the meeting. The regulations at the time of the meeting will determine how many can attend or if it will be conducted virtually.

To view our annual invitation visit https://www.southwestschools.org/about-our-district/alumni-association-7/ . We still encourage members to send their dues and consider donating to our scholarship fund. Scholarships will still be awarded as usual this year as usual.

Be safe and stay healthy!

We hope that you are continuing to live out our four core values, despite our distance!

During the upcoming week, take pictures highlighting students performing acts of TRUST, RESPECT, OWNERSHIP, AND LEADERSHIP. Post them on Twitter, Instagram and Facebook using the hashtag #ConnectingWildcats or email them to mia.neckel@southwestschools.org using “Core Values Challenge” in the subject line. Please also include your neighborhood or area of residence.

Let’s see which community can best represent what it means to be a Wildcat!

Lisa Combs Daniel
March 18 at 12:39 PM ·

Farmers Market and Food Updates:

The farmers market will still be taking place tonight with some modifications. It will be a drive-through only. We will need people to drive through the back side of the old Kmart building, and all the way around the back side of the Plaza. We will be serving people out of the back side of our building as usual just bringing the food directly to cars.

We will continue to take the Food Truck around on Tuesdays, Thursdays and Saturdays. We will do a separate post on that with the times and locations, or go to:
Notinourtown.info for the full list.

If you are a student or elderly adult in the Southwest Local area with an emergency food need, please text:
513-327-8539 for support.

We love you and are praying for all our Harrison friends.
God Bless

Lisa
Church on Fire

As the number of cases of the coronavirus, COVID-19, continues to increase across the U.S., understanding the symptoms and how they differ from other illnesses is an important step in preventing further spread.

Check out this side by side comparison of symptoms associated with coronavirus, the flu, and seasonal allergies.

UPDATE: Per the CDC, the 3 symptoms listed below are those showing up consistently across all patients with confirmed COVID-19 diagnoses, however this does not mean that some patients won't experience additional symptoms. (See our latest post on the full range of potential symptoms for more information).

You can visit our site: https://www.mercy.com/news-events/news/global/2020/mercy-health-monitoring-coronavirus-covid-19 or the CDC's dedicated COVID-19 site linked from that page for more information and the latest updates.
